\v 9 And the Leuites: both Ieshua the sonne of Azaniah, Binnui, of the sonnes of Henadad, Kadmiel;
\v 10 And their brethren, Shebaniah, Hodiiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan,
\v 11 Micah, Rehob, Hashabiah,
\v 12 Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah,
\v 13 Hodiiah, Bani, Beninu,
\v 14 The chiefe of the people. Parosh, Pahath-Moab, Elam, Zatthu, Bani,
\v 15 Bunni, Azgad, Bebai,
\v 16 Adoniiah, Biguai, Adin,
\v 17 Ater, Hizkiiah, Azzur,
\v 18 Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai,
\v 19 Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai,
\v 20 Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir,
\v 21 Meshezabeel, Zadok, Iaddua,
\v 22 Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah,
\v 23 Hoshea, Hananiah, Hashub,
\v 24 Hallohesh, Pileha, Shobek,
\v 25 Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah,
\v 26 And Ahiiah, Hanan, Anan,
\v 27 Malluch, Harim, Baanah.
\v 28 ¶ \f + \fr 10:28 \ft Ezr.2.43\f*And the rest of the people, the Priests, the Leuites, the Porters, the singers, the Nethinims, and all they that had separated themselues from the people of the lands, vnto the Law of God, their wiues, their sonnes, and their daughters, euery one hauing knowledge, and hauing vnderstanding.
\v 29 \f + \fr 10:29 \ft Heb. by the hand of.\f*They claue to their brethren their nobles, and entred into a curse, and into an oath to walke in Gods law, which was giuen by Moses the seruant of God, and to obserue and doe all the commandements of the \nd LORD\nd* our \nd LORD\nd*, and his Iudgements, and his statutes:
\v 30 \f + \fr 10:30 \ft Exo.34.16 deut.7.3.\f*And that we would not giue our daughters vnto the people of the land, nor take their daughters for our sonnes.
\v 31 \f + \fr 10:31 \ft Exod.20. 10. leui.23. 3. deut.5. 12. nehem. 13.23.\f*\f + \fr 10:31 \ft Deut.15.2 leuit.25.4.\f*\f + \fr 10:31 \ft Heb. euery hand.\f*And \add if\add* the people of the land bring ware or any victuals on the Sabbath day, to sell, \add that\add* we would not buy it of them on the Sabbath, or on the holyday, and \add that\add* wee would leaue the seuenth yeere, and the exaction of euerie debt.
\v 32 Also we made ordinances for vs, to charge our selues yeerely, with the third part of a shekel, for the seruice of the house of our God,
\v 33 For the shew-bread, and for the continuall meate-offering, and for the continuall burnt offering, of the Sabbaths, of the new moones, for the set-feastes, and for the holy \add things\add*, and \add for\add* the sin-offerings, to make an atonement for Israel, and for all the worke of the house of our God.
\v 34 \f + \fr 10:34 \ft See num. 28. & 29. chap. and Exod.23. 19. and Leuit.19.23.\f*And we cast the lots among the priests, the Leuites, and the people, for the wood offering, to bring \add it\add* into the house of our God, after the houses of our fathers, at times appointed, yeere by yeere, to burne vpon the altar of the \nd LORD\nd* our God, as \add it is\add* written in the law:
\v 35 And to bring the first fruits of our ground, and the first fruites of all fruit of all trees, yeere by yeere, vnto the house of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 36 \f + \fr 10:36 \ft Exod.13. 2. Leuit.23. 17. num. 15.19. and 18.12. &c.\f*Also the first-borne of our sonnes, and of our cattell (as \add it is\add* written in the lawe) and the firstlings of our heards, and of our flockes, to bring to the house of our God, vnto the priests that minister in the house of our God:
\v 37 And \add that\add* we should bring the first fruits of our dough, and our offerings, and the fruit of all maner of trees, of wine and of oile, vnto the priests, to the chambers of the house of our God, and the tithes of our ground vnto the Leuites, that the same Leuites might haue the tithes, in all the cities of our tillage.
\v 38 \f + \fr 10:38 \ft Num.18. 26.\f*And the priest the sonne of Aaron, shall be with the Leuites, when the Leuites take tithes, and the Leuites shal bring vp the tithe of the tithes vnto the house of our God, to the chambers into the treasure house.
\v 39 For the children of Israel, and the children of Leui, shall bring the offering of the corne, of the new wine, and the oyle, vnto the chambers, where \add are\add* the vessels of the sanctuarie, and the priests that minister, and the porters, and the singers, and we will not forsake the house of our God.
\c 11
\v 0 1 The rulers, voluntary men, and the tenth man chosen by Lot, dwell at Ierusalem. 3 A catalogue of their names. 20 The residue dwell in other cities.
\v 1 ¶ And the rulers of the people dwelt at Ierusalem: the rest of the people also cast lots, to bring one of tenne, to dwell in Ierusalem, the holy citie, and nine parts \add to dwell\add* in \add other\add* cities.
\v 2 And the people blessed all the men, that willingly offered themselues, to dwell at Ierusalem.
\v 3 ¶ Now these \add are\add* the chiefe of the prouince that dwelt in Ierusalem: but in the cities of Iudah dwelt euerie one in his possession in their cities, \add to wit\add*, Israel, the priests, and the Leuites, and the Nethinims, and the children of Solomons seruants.
\v 4 And at Ierusalem dwelt \add certaine\add* of the children of Iudah, and of the children of Beniamin. Of the children of Iudah: Athaiah the sonne of Uzziah, the sonne of Zechariah, the sonne of Amariah, the sonne of Shephatiah, the sonne of Mahalaleel, of the children of Perez.
\v 5 And Maaseiah the sonne of Baruch the sonne of Col-Hozeh, the sonne of Hazaiah the sonne of Adaiah, the sonne of Ioiarib, the sonne of Zechariah, the sonne of Shiloni.
\v 6 All the sonnes of Perez that dwelt at Ierusalem, \add were\add* foure hundred threescore and eight valiant men.
\v 7 And these \add are\add* the sonnes of Beniamin: Sallu the sonne of Meshullam, the sonne of Ioed, the sonne of Pedaiah, the sonne of Kolaiah, the sonne of Maaseiah, the sonne of Ithiel, the sonne of Iesaiah.
\v 8 And after him Gabai, Sallai, nine hundred twentie and eight.
\v 9 And Ioel the sonne of Zichri \add was\add* their ouerseer: and Iudah the sonne of Senuah, \add was\add* second ouer the city.
\v 10 Of the Priests: Iedaiah the sonne of Ioiarib, Iachin;
\v 11 Seraiah the sonne of Hilkiah, the sonne of Meshullam, the sonne of Zadok, the sonne of Meraioth, the sonne of Ahitub, \add was\add* the ruler of the house of God.
\v 12 And their brethren that did the worke of the house, \add were\add* eight hundred twentie and two: and Adaiah the sonne of Ieroham, the sonne of Pelaliah, the sonne of Amzi, the sonne of Zechariah, the sonne of Pashur, the sonne of Malchiah,
\v 13 And his brethren, chiefe of the fathers, two hundred fourty and two: and Amashai the sonne of Azareel, the sonne of Ahasai, the sonne of Meshilemoth, the sonne of Immer.
\v 14 \f + \fr 11:14 \ft Or, the sonne of Haggedodolim.\f*And their brethren mighty men of valour, an hundred twenty and eight; and their ouerseer \add was\add* Zaddiel, the sonne of \add one of\add* the great men.
\v 15 Also of the Leuites: Shemaiah the sonne of Hashub, the sonne of Azrikam, the sonne of Hashabiah, the sonne of Bunni.
\v 16 \f + \fr 11:16 \ft Hebr. were ouer.\f*And Shabbethai, and Iozabad, of the chiefe of the Leuits, \add had\add* the ouersight of the outward businesse of the house of God.
\v 17 And Mattaniah the sonne of Micha, the sonne of Zabdi, the sonne of Asaph, \add was\add* the principall to beginne the thankesgiuing in prayer: and Bakbukiah the second among his brethren, and Abda the sonne of Shammua, the sonne of Galal, the sonne of Ieduthun.
\v 18 All the Leuites in the holy City, \add were\add* two hundred, fourescore and foure.
\v 19 \f + \fr 11:19 \ft Heb. at the gates.\f*Moreouer, the porters, Akkub, Talmon, and their brethren that kept the gates, \add were\add* an hundred seuenty and two.
\v 20 ¶ And the residue of Israel, of the Priests \add and\add* the Leuites, \add were\add* in all the cities of Iudah, euery one in his inheritance.
\v 21 \f + \fr 11:21 \ft See Chap. 2.26.\f*\f + \fr 11:21 \ft Or, the tower\f*But the Nethinims dwelt in Ophel: and Ziha, and Gispa \add were\add* ouer the Nethinims.
\v 22 The ouerseer also of the Leuites at Ierusalem, \add was\add* Uzzi the sonne of Bani, the son of Hashabiah, the sonne of Mattaniah, the sonne of Micha: Of the sonnes of Asaph, the singers \add were\add* ouer the businesse of the house of God.
\v 23 \f + \fr 11:23 \ft Or, a sure ordinance.\f*For \add it was\add* the kings commandement concerning them, that a certaine portion should be for the singers, due for euery day.
\v 24 And Pethahiah the sonne of Meshezabel, of the children of Zerah the sonne of Iudah, \add was\add* at the kings hand in all matters concerning the people.
\v 25 And for the villages, with their fields, \add some\add* of the children of Iudah dwelt at Kiriath-arba, and \add in\add* the villages thereof; and at Dibon, and \add in\add* the villages thereof, and at Iekabzeel, and \add in\add* the villages thereof:
\v 26 And at Ieshua, and at Moladah, and at Beth-phelet,
\v 27 And at Hazer-Shual, and at Beer-sheba and \add in\add* the villages thereof:
\v 28 And at Ziglag, and at Mekonah, and in the villages thereof:
\v 29 And at En-Rimmon, and at Zareah, and at Iarmuth,
\v 30 Zanoah, Adullam, and \add in\add* their villages, at Lachish, and the fieldes thereof: at Azekah, and \add in\add* the villages thereof. And they dwelt from Beer-sheba, vnto the valley of Hinnom.
\v 31 \f + \fr 11:31 \ft Or, of Geba.\f*\f + \fr 11:31 \ft Or, to Michmash.\f*The children also of Beniamin, from Geba, \add dwelt\add* at Michmash, and Aiia, and Beth-el, and \add in\add* their villages:
\v 32 \add And\add* at Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah,
\v 33 Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim,
\v 34 Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat,
\v 35 Lod, and Ono, the valley of craftes-men.
\v 36 And of the Leuites, \add were\add* diuisions \add in\add* Iudah, \add and\add* in Beniamin.
\c 12
\v 0 1 The Priests, 8 and the Leuites which came vp with Zerubbabel. 10 The succession of hie Priests. 22 Certaine chiefe Leuites. 27 The solemnitie of the dedication of the walls. 44 The offices of Priests and Leuites appointed in the Temple.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 12:1 \ft Ezra 2.1.\f*Now these \add are\add* the Priests and the Leuits that went vp with Zerubbabel the sonne of Shealtiel, and Ieshua: Seraiah, Ieremiah, Ezra,
\v 2 \f + \fr 12:2 \ft Or, Melicu, ver.14.\f*Amariah, Malluch, Hattush,
\v 3 \f + \fr 12:3 \ft Or, Sebaniah, ver, 14.\f*\f + \fr 12:3 \ft Or, Harim, ver.15.\f*\f + \fr 12:3 \ft Or, Meraloth, ver.15.\f*Shecaniah, Rehum, Merimoth,
\v 4 \f + \fr 12:4 \ft Or, Ginnethon, ver. 16.\f*Iddo, Ginnetho, Abiiah,
\v 5 \f + \fr 12:5 \ft Or, Miniamin, ver. 17.\f*\f + \fr 12:5 \ft Or, Moadiah, ver.17.\f*Miamin, Madish, Bilgah,
\v 6 Shemaiah, & Ioiarib, Iedaiah,
\v 7 \f + \fr 12:7 \ft Or, Sallai, ver.20.\f*Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, Iedaiah: these \add were\add* the chiefe of the Priests, and of their brethren in the dayes of Ieshua.
\v 8 \f + \fr 12:8 \ft That is, the Psalmes of thankesgiuing.\f*Moreouer the Leuites: Ieshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Iudah, \add and\add* Mattaniah, \add which was\add* ouer the thankesgiuing, he and his brethren.
\v 9 Also Bakbukiah, and Unni; their brethren, \add were\add* ouer against them in the watches.
\v 10 ¶ And Ieshua begate Ioiakim, Ioiakim also begate Eliashib, and Eliashib begate Ioiada,
\v 11 And Ioiada begate Ionathan, and Ionathan begate Iaddua.
\v 12 And in the dayes of Ioiakim, were Priests the chiefe of the fathers: of Seraiah, Meraiah: of Ieremiah, Hananiah:
\v 13 Of Ezra, Meshullam: of Amariah, Iehohanan:
\v 14 Of Melicu, Ionathan: of Shebaniah, Ioseph:
\v 15 Of Harim, Adna: of Meraioth, Helkai:
\v 16 Of Iodo, Zechariah: of Ginnethon, Meshullam:
\v 17 Of Abijah, Zichri: of Miniamin, of Moadiah, Piltai:
\v 18 Of Bilgah, Shammua: of Shemaiah, Iehonathan:
\v 19 And of Ioiarib, Mattenai: of Iedaiah, Uzzi:
\v 20 Of Sallai, Kallai: of Amok, Eber:
\v 21 Of Hilkiah, Hashabiah: of Iedaiah, Nethanael.
\v 22 ¶ The Leuites in the dayes of Eliashib, Ioiada, and Iohanan, and Iaddua, \add were\add* recorded chiefe of the fathers: also the Priests, to the reigne of Darius the Persian.
\v 23 \f + \fr 12:23 \ft 1.Chro.9.\f*The sonnes of Leui, the chiefe of the fathers, \add were\add* written in the booke of the Chronicles, euen vntill the dayes of Iohanan the sonne of Eliashib.
\v 24 And the chiefe of the Leuites: Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and Ieshua the sonne of Kadmiel, with their brethren ouer against them, to praise \add and\add* to giue thankes, according to the commandement of Dauid the man of God, ward ouer against ward.
\v 25 \f + \fr 12:25 \ft Or, treasuries, or assemblies.\f*Mattaniah, and Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, Akkub, \add were\add* porters keeping the ward, at the thresholds of the gates.
\v 26 These \add were\add* in the dayes of Ioiakim, the sonne of Ieshua, the sonne of Iozadak, and in the dayes of Nehemiah the gouernour, and of Ezra the Priest, the Scribe.
\v 27 ¶ And at the dedication of the wall of Ierusalem, they sought the Leuites out of all their places, to bring them to Ierusalem, to keepe the dedication with gladnesse, both with thankesgiuings and with singing, \add with\add* cymbals, psalteries, and with harpes.
\v 28 And the sonnes of the Singers gathered themselues together, both out of the plaine countrey round about Ierusalem, and from the villages of Netophathi.
\v 29 Also from the house of Gilgal, and out of the fields of Geba, and Azmaueth: for the Singers had builded them villages round about Ierusalem.
\v 30 And the Priests and the Leuites purified themselues, and purified the people, and the gates, and the wall.
\v 31 Then I brought vp the princes of Iudah vpon the wall, and appointed two great \add companies of them that gaue\add* thankes, \add whereof one\add* went on the right hand vpon the wall toward the dounggate:
\v 32 And after them went Hoshaiah, and halfe of the Princes of Iudah,
\v 33 And Azariah, Ezra, and Meshullam,
\v 34 Iudah, and Beniamin, and Shemaiah, and Ieremiah,
\v 35 And \add certaine\add* of the Priests sonnes with trumpets: \add namely\add*, Zechariah the sonne of Ionathan, the sonne of Shemaiah, the sonne of Mattaniah, the sonne of Michaiah, the sonne of Zaccur, the sonne of Asaph:
\v 36 And his brethren, Shemaiah, and Asarael, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanael, and Iudah, Hanani, with the musicall instruments of Dauid the man of God; and Ezra the Scribe before them.
\v 37 And at the fountaine-gate, which was ouer against them, they went vp by the staires of the citie of Dauid, at the going vp of the wall, aboue the house of Dauid, euen vnto the water-gate, Eastward.
\v 38 And the other \add company of them that gaue\add* thankes, went ouer against \add them\add*, and I after them, and the halfe of the people vpon the wall, from beyond the towre of the fornaces, euen vnto the broad wall,
\v 39 And from aboue the gate of Ephraim, and aboue the olde gate, and aboue the fish-gate, and the towre of Hananeel, and the towre of Meah, euen vnto the sheepegate; and they stood still in the prison gate.
\v 40 So stood the two \add companies of them that gaue\add* thankes in the house of God, and I, and the halfe of the rulers with me:
\v 41 And the Priests: Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Michaiah, Elioenai, Zachariah, \add and\add* Hananiah with trumpets:
\v 42 \f + \fr 12:42 \ft Heb. made their voice to be heard.\f*And Maaseiah, and Shemaiah, and Eleazar, and Uzzi, and Iehohanan, and Malchiiah, and Elam, and Ezer. And the Singers sang loud, with Iezrahiah \add their\add* ouerseer.
\v 43 Also that day they offered great sacrifices, and reioyced; for God had made them reioyce with great ioy: the wiues also and the children reioyced: so that the ioy of Ierusalem was heard euen afarre off.
\v 44 ¶ \f + \fr 12:44 \ft That is, appointed by the law.\f*\f + \fr 12:44 \ft Hebr. for the ioy of Iudah.\f*\f + \fr 12:44 \ft Heb. that stood.\f*And at that time were some appointed ouer the chambers for the treasures, for the offerings, for the first fruits, and for the tithes, to gather into them out of the fields of the cities the portions of the law for the priests and Leuites: for Iudah reioyced for the Priests, & for the Leuites that waited.
\v 45 \f + \fr 12:45 \ft 1.Chron. 24. and 25. chap.\f*And both the singers and the porters kept the ward of their God, and the ward of the purification, according to the commandement of Dauid, \add and\add* of Solomon his sonne.
\v 46 \f + \fr 12:46 \ft 1.Chron. 25.1, &c.\f*For in the dayes of Dauid and Asaph of old, \add there were\add* chiefe of the singers, and songs of praise and thanksgiuing vnto God.
\v 47 \f + \fr 12:47 \ft That is, set apart.\f*\f + \fr 12:47 \ft Num. 18. 26.\f*And all Israel in the dayes of Zerubbabel, and in the dayes of Nehemiah, gaue the portions of the singers, and the porters, euery day his portion, and they sanctified \add holy things\add* vnto the Leuites, and the Leuites sanctified \add them\add* vnto the children of Aaron.
\c 13
\v 0 1 Vpon the reading of the Law, separation is made from the mixed multitude. 4 Nehemiah at his returne, causeth the chambers to bee cleansed. 10 He reformeth the offices in the house of God. 15 The violation of the Sabbath, 23 & the mariages with strange wiues.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 13:1 \ft Heb. there was read.\f*\f + \fr 13:1 \ft Num. 22. 5. deut.23.3\f*\f + \fr 13:1 \ft Heb. eares\f*On that day they read in the booke of Moses in the audience of the people, and therein was found written, that the Ammonite and the Moabite should not come into the Congregation of God for euer,
\v 2 \f + \fr 13:2 \ft Num. 22. 5. iosh.24.9.\f*Because they met not the children of Israel with bread, and with water, but hired Balaam against them, that he should curse them: howbeit our God turned the curse into a blessing.
\v 3 Now it came to passe when they had heard the law, that they separated from Israel all the mixed multitude.
\v 4 ¶ \f + \fr 13:4 \ft Heb. being set ouer.\f*And before this Eliashib the priest hauing the ouersight of the chamber of the house of our God, \add was\add* allied vnto Tobiah:
\v 5 \f + \fr 13:5 \ft Hebr. the commandement of the Leuites.\f*And hee had prepared for him a great chamber, where aforetime they laid the meat offrings, the frankincense and the vessels, and the tithes of the corne, the new wine, and the oile, which was commanded \add to be giuen\add* to the Leuites, and the singers, and the porters, and the offerings of the priests.
\v 6 \f + \fr 13:6 \ft Heb. at the end of daies.\f*\f + \fr 13:6 \ft Or, I earnestly requested.\f*But in all this \add time\add* was not I at Ierusalem: for in the two and thirtieth yeere of Artaxerxes king of Babylon, came I vnto the king, and after certaine dayes, obtained I leaue of the King:
\v 7 And I came to Ierusalem, and vnderstood of the euil that Eliashib did for Tobiah, in preparing him a chamber in the courts of the house of God.
\v 8 And it grieued me sore, therefore I cast foorth all the houshold stuffe of Tobiah out of the chamber:
\v 9 Then I commanded, and they cleansed the chambers, and thither brought I againe the vessels of the house of God, with the meate offering, and the frankincense.
\v 10 ¶ And I perceiued that the portions of the Leuites had not beene giuen \add them\add*: for the Leuites and the singers that did the worke, were fled euery one to his field.
\v 11 \f + \fr 13:11 \ft Heb. standing.\f*Then contended I with the rulers, and said, Why is the house of God forsaken? And I gathered them together, and set them in their place.
\v 12 \f + \fr 13:12 \ft Or, store-houses.\f*Then brought all Iudah the tithe of the corne, and the new wine, and the oyle, vnto the treasuries.
\v 13 \f + \fr 13:13 \ft Hebr. at their hand.\f*\f + \fr 13:13 \ft Heb. it was vpon them.\f*And I made treasurers ouer the treasuries, Shelemiah the priest, and Zadok the scribe, and of the Leuites, Pedaiah: and next to them \add was\add* Hanan the sonne of Zaccur, the sonne of Mattaniah: for they were counted faithfull, and their office \add was\add* to distribute vnto their brethren.
\v 14 \f + \fr 13:14 \ft Verse 22.\f*\f + \fr 13:14 \ft Heb. kindnesses.\f*\f + \fr 13:14 \ft Or, obseruations.\f*Remember me, O my God, concerning this, and wipe not out my good deeds, that I haue done for the house of my God, and for the offices thereof.
\v 15 ¶ In those dayes sawe I in Iudah, \add some\add* treading wine presses on the Sabbath, and bringing in sheaues, and lading asses, as also wine, grapes, and figs, and all maner of burdens, which they brought into Ierusalem on the Sabbath day: and I testified \add against them\add* in the day wherein they solde victuals.
\v 16 There dwelt men of Tyre also therein, which brought fish and all maner of ware, and solde on the Sabbath vnto the children of Iudah, and in Ierusalem.
\v 17 Then I contended with the Nobles of Iudah, and sayd vnto them, What euill thing \add is\add* this that ye doe, and profane the Sabbath day?
\v 18 Did not your fathers thus, and did not our God bring all this euill vpon vs, and vpon this citie? yet ye bring more wrath vpon Israel, by profaning the Sabbath.
\v 19 And it came to passe, that when the gates of Ierusalem beganne to be darke before the Sabbath, I commanded that the gates should be shut, and charged that they should not be opened till after the Sabbath: and \add some\add* of my seruants set I at the gates, \add that\add* there should no burden be brought in on the Sabbath day.
\v 20 So the merchants, and sellers of all kinde of ware, lodged without Ierusalem once or twice.
\v 21 \f + \fr 13:21 \ft Heb. before the wall.\f*Then I testified against them, and said vnto them, Why lodge yee about the wall? If ye doe \add so\add* againe, I will lay hands on you. From that time forth came they no \add more\add* on the Sabbath.
\v 22 \f + \fr 13:22 \ft Or, multitude.\f*And I commanded the Leuites, that they should cleanse themselues, and \add that\add* they should come \add and\add* keepe the gates, to sanctifie the Sabbath day: Remember me, O my God, \add concerning\add* this also, and spare me, according to the greatnesse of thy mercie.
\v 23 ¶ \f + \fr 13:23 \ft Heb. had made to dwell with them.\f*In those dayes also sawe I Iewes \add that\add* had maried wiues of Ashdod, of Ammon, \add and\add* of Moab:
\v 24 \f + \fr 13:24 \ft Heb. they discerned not to speake.\f*\f + \fr 13:24 \ft Heb. of people and people.\f*And their children spake halfe in the speech of Ashdod, and could not speake in the Iewes language, but according to the language of ech people.
\v 25 \f + \fr 13:25 \ft Or, reuiled them.\f*And I contended with them, and cursed them, and smote certeine of them, and pluckt off their haire, and made them sweare by God, \add saying\add*, Yee shall not giue your daughters vnto their sonnes, nor take their daughters vnto your sonnes, or for your selues.
\v 26 \f + \fr 13:26 \ft 1.King.11 1, &c.\f*Did not Solomon king of Israel sinne by these things? yet among many nations was there no king like him, who was beloued of his God, and God made him king ouer all Israel: neuerthelesse, euen him did outlandish women cause to sinne.
\v 27 Shall wee then hearken vnto you, to doe all this great euill, to transgresse against our God, in marrying strange wiues?
\v 28 And \add one\add* of the sonnes of Ioiada, the sonne of Eliashib the high Priest, \add was\add* sonne in law to Sanballat the Horonite: therfore I chased him from me.
\v 29 \f + \fr 13:29 \ft Heb. for the defilings.\f*Remember them, O my God, because they haue defiled the Priesthood, and the couenant of the Priesthood, and of the Leuites.
\v 30 Thus cleansed I them from all strangers, and appointed the wards of the Priests and the Leuites, euery one in his businesse:
\v 31 And for the wood-offering, at times appointed, and for the first fruits. Remember me, O my God, for good.
